Thousands of pupils are writing their final matric exams. But with the added stress, what can pupils do to best survive this period? Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - With the end-of-year exam season underway, parents have been urged to help their children manage their stress levels. In previous years, the stress of exams has driven pupils to take their own lives. Akeso hospitals' social worker Megan Hosking says it's critical that children prepare adequately and seek help, when they are not coping. "If you find that you are struggling to cope, help is available.” READ: Lesufi: Everything in place for 2019 Matric exams Tips for reducing exam stress Tips for parents and caregivers  